    • Method Detail

      • changeRowColor

        boolean changeRowColor()
        If false is returned, the unpagedListDisplay rendering the dto will use the color of the previous row when it renders the row representing this particular instance of the dto.
        Returns:
        true if the row should change colors, false otherwise

      • greyOutRow

        boolean greyOutRow()
        If false is returned, row is rendered normally. Else, row is rendered "greyed-out"
        Returns:
        true if row should be greyed out, false otherwise

      • getNodeIdString

        java.lang.String getNodeIdString()
        Returns:
        a id string in the form of "p*id*" or "c*id* depending on whether or not the node is considered a child or not
